List 10 real-life AI applications you use daily and explain how ML might work behind each in 1–2 lines.

Phone face unlock
Your phone learns what your face looks like and checks if the face in front of it matches.
Google search
Google tries to understand what you mean, not just the words you type, and shows results people usually click.
YouTube / Instagram reels
The app watches what you like, skip, or replay, then shows you similar stuff to keep you watching.
Keyboard autocorrect
Your phone guesses the word you’re trying to type based on what most people usually type next.
Google Maps
It looks at live traffic and past traffic to guess the fastest route.
Spam calls (Truecaller / Phone app)
If many people mark a number as spam, the app learns to warn others.
Photo gallery face grouping
Your phone notices similar faces in photos and puts the same person’s photos together.
Gmail spam emails
Emails that look like past spam emails are automatically sent to spam.
Camera night mode / portrait
The camera software fixes dark or blurry photos and focuses better on faces.
Amazon / Flipkart suggestions
Shopping apps show products based on what you searched or bought earlier






























